# Bulk empirical sweep TSVs from the libwebp parity audit (PR #37).
# Regeneratable via `dev/empirical_sweep.rs` against a CID22 / CLIC /
# ImageMagick corpus. Kept on block storage at /mnt/v/output/zenwebp/audit/
# rather than in git — they add ~720 KB of compressed pack churn for data
# that's a single command away. The summary in
# `differences/05-empirical-analysis.md` is what callers actually consume;
# the per-batch baselines under `differences/baselines/` are the audit
# progression.
differences/05-empirical-*.tsv

# Large picker training artifacts — committed only as small JSON manifests; raw weights + sweep TSVs live ephemerally
benchmarks/zenwebp_pareto_*.tsv
benchmarks/zenwebp_pareto_features_*.tsv
benchmarks/zenwebp_hybrid_*.json
benchmarks/zenwebp_hybrid_*.log
benchmarks/zenwebp_pareto_features_2026-04-29_v0.1.0.tsv.bak
benchmarks/zenwebp_pareto_features_2026-04-29.tsv.bak
benchmarks/picker_ab_*.tsv
benchmarks/zenwebp_picker_v0.*.bin
benchmarks/zenwebp_picker_v0.*.manifest.json
benchmarks/zenwebp_bake_*.log

# Pareto sweep parquets — large oracle artifacts, live in /mnt/v + tower
benchmarks/*.parquet

# Cloudflare Workers / Wrangler local state — picked up if `wrangler dev`
# is ever run inside the repo. Never commit.
.wrangler/
